===Alternative forms===
* In [[Traditional Chinese]], Japanese [[kyūjitai]], Korean [[hanja]], the component {{m|mul|𦰩}} for this character is written with {{l|mul|廿}} on top. Note that the bottom portion is written {{l|mul|口}} overlapped by {{l|mul|夫}} and not {{l|mul|中}} on top of {{l|mul|天}}.
* In Vietnamese [[Hán Nôm]], {{m|mul|𦰩}} can be written with {{l|mul|廿}}, {{l|mul|龷}}, or {{l|mul|艹}} on top. But the most common variant of {{m|mul|𦰩}} is with {{l|mul|龷}} written on top.
* In Japanese [[shinjitai]], the component {{m|mul|𦰩}} is written with <big>{{l|mul|sc=Jpan|艹}}</big> on top and has one stroke less. Due to [[w:Han unification|Han unification]], both traditional Chinese and Japanese shinjitai forms are encoded under the same [[code point]]. The appearance of this character will differ depending on the font used.
* In [[Simplified Chinese]], the component {{m|mul|𦰩}} is simplified to {{l|mul|又}} instead, giving the character {{l|mul|汉}} (<code>U+6C49</code>).
* Two [[w:CJK Compatibility Ideographs|compatibility ideographs]] exist for this character. <code>U+FA47</code> corresponds to the [[kyūjitai]] form of this character while <code>U+FA9A</code> corresponds to the alternative form used in North Korea which is similar to Japanese shinjitai.

